50|$|The 1995 Chicago <b>heat</b> <b>wave</b> was a <b>heat</b> <b>wave</b> {{which led}} to 739 heat-related deaths in Chicago {{over a period of}} five days. Most of the victims of the <b>heat</b> <b>wave</b> were elderly poor {{residents}} of the city, who could not afford air conditioning and did not open windows or sleep outside for fear of crime. The <b>heat</b> <b>wave</b> also heavily impacted the wider Midwestern region, with additional deaths in both St. Louis, Missouri and Milwaukee, Wisconsin.|$|R
