50|$|The 2009 Pacific Northwest <b>heat</b> <b>wave</b> was a <b>heat</b> <b>wave</b> that {{affected}} the Pacific Northwest {{region of the}} United States and Canada in late July 2009, particularly areas west of the Cascade Mountains in British Columbia, Oregon and Washington. The <b>heat</b> <b>wave</b> set many new heat records across the area, and broke the previous all-time record-high temperature in Seattle by three Fahrenheit degrees (1.7 Celsius degrees). Because the temperatures reached in the <b>heat</b> <b>wave</b> are rare in the Pacific Northwest, few residents own air conditioners.|$|R
